      <body>
         <div type="bibliography">
            <listBibl type="editions">
               <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Budge1896Alexander1"/>
                  <citedRange>355-276</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </listBibl>
            <listBibl type="translation">
               <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Budge1896AlexanderTranslation"/>
                  <citedRange>555-584</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </listBibl>
            <listBibl type="secondary">
               <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Haelewyck2016Rechabites"/>
               </bibl>
            </listBibl>
         </div>
         <div type="edition">
            <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit" xml:lang="gez">
               <ab>
                  ስምዑ፡ አኀዊነ፡ ንዜንወክሙ፡ ዜና፡ ሐዲዘ፡ ዜናሆሙ፡ ለብፁዓን፡ ቅዱሳን፡ ጻድቃን፡ ዘኮኑ፡ በመዋዕለ፡ ኤርምያስ፡ ነቢይ፡  
                  <gap reason="omitted"/> ወነግሠ፡ ፩ንጉሥ፡ ዘስሙ፡ ሴዴቅያስ፡
               </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" subtype="explicit" xml:lang="gez">
               <ab>
                  ወአንበረ፡ ውስተ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ዮሐንስ፡ መጥምቅ። ስብሐት፡ ለአብ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/> ዘከሠተ፡ ሎሙ፡ ምሥጢራተ፡ 
                  <gap reason="omitted"/> እምርስሐተ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ዓለም፡ ኀላፊ፡ በምሕረተ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/>
               </ab>
            </div>
            <note>The following division into textparts is based on <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Brankaer2016VersionEthiopienne"/>
               </bibl>.</note>
            <div type="textpart" subtype="part" xml:lang="gez" xml:id="Part1">
               <label>History of the Blessed at the time of Jeremiah</label>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" subtype="part" xml:lang="gez" xml:id="Part2">
               <label>
                  <persName ref="PRS1666Alexande"/> discovers the Island of the Blessed</label>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" subtype="part" xml:lang="gez" xml:id="Part3">
               <label>The monk Gerasimas is lead to the Island of the Blessed after having read about it in a History of Alexander</label>
            </div>
